               <head>JOHN CHRYSOSTOM; S. X </head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <note>On 1r is a list (s. xiv?) of texts to be read on certain feast days, and in the MS itself the upper margin of the first page of homilies to be read accordingly has a corresponding note. On fol. 1r there is also a note by the main scribe in majuscules, perhaps a pen-trial: δύναται καί είς τούς άγίους τρεϊς παϊδας ιδτορία.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus>(fol. 2rv)</locus>
                     <title type="desc">A list of the contents</title>
                     <note>ending impf. in art. 13.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus>(fols. 3r-326r)</locus>
                     <author key="person_297475745">John Chrysostom</author>
                     <msItem>
